DataElement.preferredDefinition: The number that represents the percent purity of the compound.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: A substance formed by chemical union of two or more elements or ingredients in definite proportion by weight._A unit for expressing a number as a fraction of hundred (on the basis of a rate or proportion per hundred)._A quantitative assessment of the homogeneity or uniformity of a mixture. Alternatively, purity refers to the degree of being free of contaminants or heterogeneous components.

ConceptualDomain.preferredDefinition: A category of organic or inorganic substances, elements, and isotopes used in research or for the prevention, diagnosis, and/or treatment of disease states. Includes biologically active substances that are either synthetically manufactured or endogenous substances extracted and processed to be reintroduced into an organism. Chemicals and drugs also include hazardous substances, and naturally occurring or synthetically produced substances required to maintain life.
